name: Another 24 Hours
notes:
New Closed Meeting of AA


Originally published in 1952, Twelve Steps and
Twelve Traditions, the 12 and 12, is used by A.A.
members and groups around the world. It lays
out the principles by which A.A. members
recover and by which the fellowship functions.
The basic text clarifies the Steps which
constitute the A.A. way of life and the Traditions,
by which A.A. maintains its unity.



‣ First Friday: Step Reading

‣ Second Friday: Step Reading

‣ Third Friday: Speaker about Step

‣ Fourth Friday: Tradition Meeting

Doubletree.


Please use the front door.

The meeting is held in the Parlor.
